# Rules for AI

This file provides guidance to AI Agent when working with code in this repository.

## Commands

- `npm run dev` ‚Äî start the Astro dev server (Vite, Node runtime)
- `npm run build` ‚Äî production build (SSR via `@astrojs/vercel`)
- `npm run preview` ‚Äî preview the production build
- `npm run lint` ‚Äî ESLint with type-checked rules
- `npm run lint:fix` ‚Äî auto-fix lint issues
- `npm run format` ‚Äî Prettier (includes prettier-plugin-astro + prettier-plugin-tailwindcss)

No test runner is configured yet.

Pre-commit hooks: husky + lint-staged runs `eslint --fix` on `*.{ts,tsx,astro}` and `prettier --write` on `*.{json,css,md}`.

## Architecture

**Astro 6 SSR app** with React 19 islands, Tailwind 4, Supabase auth, and shadcn/ui components. Deployed to Vercel via the `@astrojs/vercel` adapter.

### Rendering mode

Full server-side rendering (`output: "server"` in astro.config.mjs). All pages are server-rendered by default. API routes that should not be prerendered must export `const prerender = false`.

### Auth flow

- `src/lib/supabase.ts` ‚Äî `createClient(headers, cookies)` builds a Supabase SSR client (`@supabase/ssr`, cookie-based sessions). It reads `SUPABASE_URL`/`SUPABASE_KEY` from `astro:env/server` and **returns `null` when either is missing** ‚Äî every caller must handle the null case.
- `src/middleware.ts` ‚Äî runs on every request, resolves the current user, attaches `context.locals.user` (typed in `src/env.d.ts`). Redirects unauthenticated users away from routes listed in `PROTECTED_ROUTES`.
- API endpoints: `src/pages/api/auth/{signin,signup,signout}.ts`
- Auth pages: `src/pages/auth/{signin,signup,confirm-email}.astro`
- Protected page example: `src/pages/dashboard.astro`

### Graceful degradation when Supabase is unconfigured

`SUPABASE_URL`/`SUPABASE_KEY` are declared **optional** in the `astro:env` schema, so the app builds and runs without them. `src/lib/config-status.ts` exposes `missingConfigs`, which the UI surfaces as a warning (Polish copy) when auth is disabled. Don't assume the Supabase client exists ‚Äî guard on the `null` return from `createClient`.

### Key conventions

- **Path alias**: `@/*` maps to `./src/*` (tsconfig paths).
- **Astro components** for static content/layout; **React components** only when interactivity is needed.
- **Tailwind class merging**: use the `cn()` helper from `@/lib/utils` (clsx + tailwind-merge) for conditional/merged class names. Do not concatenate class strings manually.
- **shadcn/ui**: components live in `src/components/ui/`, "new-york" style variant. Install new ones with `npx shadcn@latest add [name]`. Hooks alias is `@/hooks`.
- **API routes**: use uppercase `GET`, `POST` exports; validate input with zod.
- **Supabase migrations**: place in `supabase/migrations/` using naming format `YYYYMMDDHHmmss_short_description.sql`. Always enable RLS on new tables with granular per-operation, per-role policies. (Currently the project uses only Supabase Auth's built-in `auth.users`; no app migrations exist yet.)
- **React**: no Next.js directives ("use client" etc.). Extract hooks to `src/components/hooks/`.
- **Services/helpers** go in `src/lib/` (or `src/lib/services/` for extracted business logic).
- **Shared types** (entities, DTOs) go in `src/types.ts`.

### Environment

- Node.js v22.14.0 (see `.nvmrc`)
- Env vars: `SUPABASE_URL`, `SUPABASE_KEY` ‚Äî copy `.env.example` to `.env` (both optional; auth is disabled if unset)
- Local Supabase: `npx supabase start` (requires Docker). Local Studio at `http://localhost:54323`.
- Deploy: handled by Vercel. Set `SUPABASE_URL`/`SUPABASE_KEY` as project environment variables in the Vercel dashboard.

## CI

GitHub Actions workflow (`.github/workflows/ci.yml`) runs on every push and PR to `master`: `npm ci` ‚Üí `npx astro sync` ‚Üí `npm run lint` ‚Üí `npm run build`. The build step needs `SUPABASE_URL` and `SUPABASE_KEY` repository secrets.
